Valuation — flag overvalued names by P/E and P/B within their sector and own history; use forward-looking PEG (≤~1 attractive, >2 expensive) rather than trailing P/E alone for growth names
Earnings quality — flag declining revenue/profit, margin erosion, or cash flow (CFO) running below reported net income
Dividend yield — list consistent income generators; treat unusually high yield as a possible warning, not a positive
Governance red flags — promoter pledging (0% ideal; >15% concerning, >50% serious), auditor resignations/changes, heavy related-party transactions, equity dilution, declining promoter holding
Cite India data sources where useful (Screener.in, Trendlyne, NSE/BSE shareholding filings)

